summary: An ordinance providing for the acquisition and repossession by the City of Seattle for use a public street of a strip of land 52 feet in width extending along the east boundary line of block 368, Seattle Tide Lands, from a line 3 feet south of the north line of lot 5, produced east 52 feet to a line 15 feet south of the south line of lot 14 produced east 52 feet to the east line of said strip, and authorizing and directing the Board of Public Works to serve notice on Moran Brothers Company, a corporation to remove from said premises.
